description.en:
This ontology covers the assets and condition assesment of a sewage system, mirroring the elements as defined per the national advisory leaflet DWA-M 150 of German sewage systems.

https://shop.dwa.de/DWA-M-150-Datenaustauschformat-fuer-die-Zustandserfassung-von-Entwaesserungssystemen-April-2010-Stand-korrigierte-Fassung-November-2018/M-150-10

This ontology was created as part of a Bachelors Thesis into an investigation of existing ontologies for underground infrastructure.

abstract.value:
Underground sewage infrastructure maintenance faces challenges due to fragmented, analog asset data, hindering effective real-time monitoring and predictive maintenance. While digital twins offer promising technological potential, their practical implementation is constrained by complex data integration challenges. Ontologies emerge as a critical approach to establish data relationships, providing a structured framework for bridging these systemic information gaps.

To address these gaps, this thesis introduces M150-Onto, a novel ontology designed to enhance the data management of sewage infrastructure by aligning with German regulatory frameworks and supporting interoperability among diverse data sources. This work explores an ontological approach with a particular focus on enabling more efficient querying and reasoning capabilities, allowing for advanced data retrieval and automated inference to support sewer infrastructure data management. M150-Onto is developed and tested within Protégé, demonstrating its potential to improve data accessibility, integration, and predictive maintenance strategies. By identifying the strengths and limitations of current ontological frameworks and proposing M150-Onto as a targeted solution, this research contributes to the digital transformation of sewage infrastructure management. The emphasis on efficient querying and reasoning enhances data-driven decision-making and sustainable maintenance strategies, addressing the critical need for improved infrastructure management amidst growing urbanization and environmental pressures.

comment.en:
The taxonomy of references includes the reference tables found in the advisory leaflet DWA-M 150.

DWA-M 150 categorizes reference tables by type of data. Examples are:
- Reference Table 105: Material Types (Class/Subclass: Reference/Material)
- Reference Table 202: Condition Assessment Coding Systems (Reference/CodingSystem)

Each subclass refers to a specific reference table in DWA-M 150, implied with the equivalentTo axiom "hasReferenceTable value "[RefTableNumber]"".

The different types found within a reference table are then listed as subclasses of the aforementioned subclass.

comment.de:
Die Komponententaxonomie umfasst die Hauptkomponenten eines Kanalisationssystems gemäß dem Merkblatt DWA-M 150 und der Referenztabelle 128 "Objekttypen".

Es wird empfohlen, Individuen für Haltungsabschnitte mit der Vorlage zu erstellen:

PipeSection[PipeSectionDesignation]
PipeSection[HG001]

Es wird empfohlen, Individuen für Knoten mit der Vorlage zu erstellen:

Node[NodeDesignation]
Node[KG001]

Es wird ebenfalls empfohlen, zu deklarieren, dass Komponenten zu einer anderen Komponente mit der asymmetrischen/ irreflexiven Unterobjekteigenschaft flowsTo (Invers: flowsFrom) fließen.

Die Ontologie sollte dann automatisch folgern, dass alle Komponenten, die zu/von einander fließen, verbunden sind — mit ihrer transitiven Überobjekteigenschaft "connectedWith".

Revision 1 Aug 2025: NodeStructure wurde als Unterklasse von Node hinzugefügt. Diese Strukturen reflektieren <KA> innerhalb einer M150-XML-Datei.
comment.en:
The taxonomy of components includes the main components of a sewage system according to the advisory leaflet DWA-M 150 and the reference table 128 "Object Types".

It is recommended to create individuals for Pipe Sections with the template:

` PipeSection[PipeSectionDesignation] `
` PipeSection[HG001] `

It is recommended to create individuals for Nodes with the template:

` Node[NodeDesignation] `
` Node[KG001] `

It is also recommended to declare that Components flows to another component with the asymmetric/irreflexive sub-object property `flowsTo` (Inverse: flowsFrom).

The ontology should then automatically reason, that all components flowing to / from each other are connected -- with its transitive super-object property "connectedWith".

Revision 1 Aug 2025: NodeStructure added as a Subclass of Node. These structures reflect <KA> within an M150-XML.

The taxonomy of geometry includes the GIS geometry data of M150-Components. These include Geometry Object and Geometry Points.

It is recommended to create individuals for geometric objects with the template:

` GeoObject[PipeSection/Node Designation] `
` GeoObject[HG001]  ` for Pipe Section: Geometry Objects;
` GeoObject[KG001] ` for Node: Geometry Objects.

It is recommended to create individuals for geometric points with the template:

` GeoPoint[Geometry Point Description] `
` GeoPoint[GP001]  `.

`GeoObject`'s should be declared as the parent of 'GeoPoint''s with the object property `isParentOf`. (Inverse: isChildOf)

`GeoObject`'s should be declared as the renderer of a Component with the object property 'renders'. (Inverse: renderedBy)

The taxonomy of reports includes inspection and condition reports for a sewage system, according to the structure of the advisory leaflet DWA-M 150.

It is recommended to create individuals for inspection reports with the template:

` Inspection[PipeSectionDesignation]_[Date] `;
` Inspection[HG001]_[HI003] ` for Pipe Section: Inspection reports;
` Inspection[KG001]_[KI003] ` for Node: Inspection reports.

It is recommended to create individuals for condition reports within an inspection with the template:

` Condition[PipeSectionDesignation]_[Stationing(ConditionReport)]_[Code] `;
` Condition[HG001]_[HZ001]_[HZ002] ` for Pipe Section: Condition reports;
` Condition[HG001]_[KZ001]_[KZ002] ` for Node: Condition reports.

According to the DWA-M 150, the coding systems that can be applied here are:
- DIN EN 13508-2
- DWA 149-2
- DWA ATV-M 143
- ISYBAU2001
- ISYBAU1996

A NodeStructure refers to the <KA> element in DWA M150-XML.

It is recommended to set a NodeStructure as isChildOf the Node it is nested in.

Naming Convention:
` NodeStructure_[KG001]_[KA001] `

With KG001 being the Node it is nested in.

A node is a component in a sewage system that serves as a junction for pipes. It's often where manholes or access points are located.

It is recommended to create individuals for Nodes with the template:

` Node[NodeDesignation] `
` Node[KG001] `
Used in Class Condition (Template: "Condition[HG001]_[ConditionStation]_[Code]" isChildOf Inspection)
A Component is renderedBy a Geometry
Superclass for TopNodes and BottomNodes classification (HG003, HG004, HG005)
